         <abstract>
            <p>Using a test statistic which specifically allows for parameter shifts over time, we investigate the time-variance relationship of security returns. The null hypothesis of stationary and independent increments is rejected, and the existence of a complex short-term reversal phenomenon is reported.</p>
         </abstract>
